[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":46},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Ftags\u002FSCSS-Handbook\u002F":3,"tag-page:en:SCSS-Handbook:1":4,"author-stats:en:full":43},null,{"tag":5,"slug":6,"posts":7,"total":41,"totalPages":42},"SCSS Handbook","SCSS-Handbook",[8,16,22,29,35],{"url":9,"title":10,"date":11,"updated":3,"category":12,"tags":13,"description":14,"readingMinutes":15},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F","SCSS Handbook (5) — mixin","2019-04-21 07:24:30","SCSS",[12,5],"The previous post covered `@import`. This one starts pulling in earlier topics, building up to `mixin`. What's a mixin? I think of it as an SCSS library — a place to store frequently used SCSS snippets.","2",{"url":17,"title":18,"date":19,"updated":3,"category":12,"tags":20,"description":21,"readingMinutes":15},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F","SCSS Handbook (4) — @import","2019-04-19 17:24:30",[12,5],"SCSS provides `@import`, which makes development management way easier when used well.",{"url":23,"title":24,"date":25,"updated":3,"category":12,"tags":26,"description":27,"readingMinutes":28},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F","SCSS Handbook (3) — Operators","2019-04-18 17:24:30",[12,5],"Operators? Like add, subtract, multiply, divide? Yep — SCSS supports operators: add (+), subtract (-), multiply (*), and divide (\u002F).","1",{"url":30,"title":31,"date":32,"updated":3,"category":12,"tags":33,"description":34,"readingMinutes":15},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F","SCSS Handbook (2) — Variables ($)","2019-04-17 12:45:50",[12,5],"From this post on we won't talk about SASS — let's focus on the SCSS basics.",{"url":36,"title":37,"date":38,"updated":3,"category":12,"tags":39,"description":40,"readingMinutes":15},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F16\u002Fscss-handbook-1-intro\u002F","SCSS Handbook (1) — Intro","2019-04-16 20:03:12",[12,5],"First, big thanks to Hexschool's principal Liao Wei-Chieh for writing \"30 Days to Master SASS Syntax\", which I keep coming back to as I learn SCSS — it's a real godsend.",5,1,{"postCount":44,"tagCount":45},1034,1042,1784020380741]